<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - CAB - TILT: 9600 AND 9700 SLEEPER AND NON-SLEEPER CABS -
        CAB DOOR ADJUSTMENT
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec id="hl1600612">
        <title>CAB DOOR ADJUSTMENT</title>
        <svcsubsecinfo>
            <para>When a door adjustment is required, you will need to know where the various adjustments are located
                and what effect each adjustment has on door fit. These adjustments apply whether door has been replaced
                or adjustment is simply being made to improve the door to frame fit or operation.
            </para>
        </svcsubsecinfo>
        <svcproc svcproctype="adjust" graphiccount="2">
            <title>HINGE PILLAR ADJUSTMENT (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1600646">Figure 46</hotlnk>and
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1600647">Figure 47</hotlnk>)
            </title>
            <figure id="f1600646" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1600646" filename="../figg16/g1600646.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 46. Location for Cab Door Adjustment</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. DOOR HINGE PILLAR</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. CAB DOOR HINGE</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f1600647" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1600647" filename="../figg16/g1600647.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 47. Details of Cab Door Hinge</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. ADJUSTING SHIMS</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. ELONGATED HOLES</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. HINGE BACK SIDE</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. HINGE FACE SIDE</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Forward and rearward door adjustments are made by shims located between door half of
                    hinge and door.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Up and down door adjustment is made at elongated holes in door half of hinge.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">In and out door adjustment is made at enlarged holes and floating tapping blocks in side
                    of door.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">With mounting bolts slightly loosened, adjust hinge so as to center door in opening with
                    a slight pressure on weatherseal. Then tighten screws to 180 in-lbs. (20 N&#8226;m).
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
